    • Float3DirectedGraph

      public Float3DirectedGraph(boolean[][][] validGrid, float defaultEdgeWeight)
      Given a 3D boolean array, adds a vertex where a cell in validGrid is true, or ignores it otherwise. This only adds vertices.
      Parameters:
      validGrid - a 3D boolean array where true means to add that vertex; may be jagged, but this will just use its largest dimensions then
      defaultEdgeWeight - the default edge weight to use when a weight is unspecified

    • Float3DirectedGraph

      public Float3DirectedGraph(char[][][] validGrid, char validChar, float defaultEdgeWeight)
      Given a 3D char array, adds a vertex where a cell in validGrid is equal to validChar, or ignores it otherwise. This only adds vertices.
      Parameters:
      validGrid - a 3D char array where validChar means to add that vertex; may be jagged, but this will just use its largest dimensions then
      validChar - the char that, when found in validGrid, means a vertex will be added
      defaultEdgeWeight - the default edge weight to use when a weight is unspecified

    • Float3DirectedGraph

      public Float3DirectedGraph(float[][][] validGrid, float minimumThreshold, float maximumThreshold, float defaultEdgeWeight)
      Given a 3D float array, adds a vertex where a cell in validGrid has a value between minimumThreshold and maximumThreshold, both inclusive, or ignores it otherwise. This only adds vertices.
      Parameters:
      validGrid - a 3D float array; may be jagged, but this will just use its largest dimensions then
      minimumThreshold - the minimum inclusive value in validGrid to allow as a vertex
      maximumThreshold - the maximum inclusive value in validGrid to allow as a vertex
      defaultEdgeWeight - the default edge weight to use when a weight is unspecified
